00:03:08.856 --> 00:03:10.424 align:middle line:84%
about their religious
enterprise,

00:03:10.424 --> 00:03:12.960 align:middle line:84%
or as atheists saying
the religions are definitely

00:03:12.960 --> 00:03:14.528 align:middle line:90%
flawed. They're wrong.

00:03:14.528 --> 00:03:15.930 align:middle line:90%
So this is reality.

00:03:15.930 --> 00:03:17.932 align:middle line:84%
We're living in a world where
the majority

00:03:17.932 --> 00:03:20.134 align:middle line:90%
of youngsters now can no longer

00:03:20.134 --> 00:03:22.236 align:middle line:84%
relate to a prescriptive
religion.

00:03:22.236 --> 00:03:24.038 align:middle line:84%
Hinduism or Christianity
or whatever.

00:03:24.038 --> 00:03:26.006 align:middle line:90%
This is reality.

00:03:26.006 --> 00:03:29.543 align:middle line:84%
>> Lilou: So how, because I saw
your talks on quantum physics,

00:03:29.543 --> 00:03:33.547 align:middle line:84%
how is quantum physics
related to the spiritual world?

00:03:33.547 --> 00:03:36.650 align:middle line:84%
>> Lakhani: Suppose I was
talking to the elite thinking

00:03:36.650 --> 00:03:38.485 align:middle line:84%
youngsters in this country, at
MIT, at Oxford University

00:03:38.485 --> 00:03:40.020 align:middle line:84%
and Eatong College,
et cetera,

00:03:40.020 --> 00:03:41.922 align:middle line:84%
and suppose I said look,
here is this, you know,

00:03:41.922 --> 00:03:45.159 align:middle line:84%
this marvelous scripture of the
ancient Hindus, and we talk

00:03:45.159 --> 00:03:47.861 align:middle line:84%
about this and they run away
from me. But if I say look,

00:03:47.861 --> 00:03:50.831 align:middle line:84%
I come from a science lobby
and not a hippy science

00:03:50.831 --> 00:03:53.734 align:middle line:84%
but, I feel, a very mainstream
science lobby.

00:03:53.734 --> 00:03:56.570 align:middle line:84%
I studied physics at Imperial
College and specialized

00:03:56.570 --> 00:03:58.806 align:middle line:84%
in quantum mechanics, which
is supposed to be very stylish

00:03:58.806 --> 00:04:02.309 align:middle line:84%
and esoteric physics, and I did
it under somebody very famous,

00:04:02.309 --> 00:04:03.510 align:middle line:90%
Roger Penrose,

00:04:03.510 --> 00:04:05.813 align:middle line:84%
who is probably the second
most important physicist

00:04:05.813 --> 00:04:07.982 align:middle line:84%
in the country. So, I come
with the right pedigree

00:04:07.982 --> 00:04:11.684 align:middle line:84%
of science pedigree so when I
present my ideas regarding what

00:04:11.684 --> 00:04:15.289 align:middle line:84%
I think is spirituality in
a format which is rational

00:04:15.289 --> 00:04:19.293 align:middle line:84%
and science oriented, of course
I steal the show.

00:04:19.293 --> 00:04:23.163 align:middle line:84%
They love me. They applaud
me very warmly and, you know,

00:04:23.163 --> 00:04:24.331 align:middle line:90%
sometimes wait in a line

00:04:24.331 --> 00:04:25.799 align:middle line:84%
to shake my hand
saying we loved that,

00:04:25.799 --> 00:04:27.768 align:middle line:84%
Mr. Lakhani! That was very
interesting.

00:04:27.768 --> 00:04:31.038 align:middle line:84%
So, in fact, the support I
get regarding my vision

00:04:31.038 --> 00:04:32.306 align:middle line:90%
about spirituality doesn't come

00:04:32.306 --> 00:04:34.842 align:middle line:84%
from antiquitious
scriptures of the Hindus,

00:04:34.842 --> 00:04:37.011 align:middle line:84%
it comes from modern
science itself

00:04:37.011 --> 00:04:40.714 align:middle line:84%
and that is why I really
find myself excited

00:04:40.714 --> 00:04:41.849 align:middle line:90%
about the whole enterprise.

00:04:41.849 --> 00:04:44.118 align:middle line:84%
>> Lilou: Is there some
point that you shifted

00:04:44.118 --> 00:04:47.287 align:middle line:84%
after your studies or you've
always been thinking that way

00:04:47.287 --> 00:04:49.657 align:middle line:84%
and yet you decided
to study science?

00:04:49.657 --> 00:04:50.624 align:middle line:90%
>> Lakhani: Yes.

00:04:50.624 --> 00:04:51.892 align:middle line:84%
You see like almost
all youngsters

00:04:51.892 --> 00:04:54.294 align:middle line:84%
of all religions you start
because in a traditional manner.

00:04:54.294 --> 00:04:56.130 align:middle line:84%
You're born in a
particular family

00:04:56.130 --> 00:04:58.065 align:middle line:84%
with a particular
religious tradition.

00:04:58.065 --> 00:05:00.134 align:middle line:84%
So you subscribe to it and
you dance about with it

00:05:00.134 --> 00:05:03.470 align:middle line:84%
and you enjoy the colorful
narratives and do the liturgy

00:05:03.470 --> 00:05:05.839 align:middle line:84%
and rituals and festivals and
it's all marvelous.

00:05:05.839 --> 00:05:08.942 align:middle line:84%
So that's how the journey
started, but when I was 15,

00:05:08.942 --> 00:05:10.644 align:middle line:90%
I started to challenge this idea

00:05:10.644 --> 00:05:12.613 align:middle line:84%
about a supreme personality
called God

00:05:12.613 --> 00:05:13.947 align:middle line:90%
who started the Creation.

00:05:13.947 --> 00:05:15.182 align:middle line:90%
I didn't agree.

00:05:15.182 --> 00:05:17.251 align:middle line:84%
I couldn't accept it
anymore so I started fighting

00:05:17.251 --> 00:05:19.253 align:middle line:84%
with my father saying
there's no God.

00:05:19.253 --> 00:05:20.454 align:middle line:90%
So I turned into an atheist.

00:05:20.454 --> 00:05:21.822 align:middle line:90%
This is reality.

00:05:21.822 --> 00:05:24.091 align:middle line:84%
I was a crass atheist saying
this whole thing is nonsense,

00:05:24.091 --> 00:05:26.994 align:middle line:84%
they put on old wives'
tales. It's not for real.

00:05:26.994 --> 00:05:29.396 align:middle line:84%
This religious enterprise
is nonsense.

00:05:29.396 --> 00:05:32.066 align:middle line:84%
So I had to fight with my
father almost regularly

00:05:32.066 --> 00:05:33.667 align:middle line:90%
and he enjoyed it.

00:05:33.667 --> 00:05:35.302 align:middle line:84%
He smiled and would respond to
me.

00:05:35.302 --> 00:05:39.807 align:middle line:84%
So at that stage, at age of 15,
I was an atheist really and then

00:05:39.807 --> 00:05:43.010 align:middle line:84%
when I became 16, 17, I
started to dig deeper.

00:05:43.010 --> 00:05:46.146 align:middle line:84%
So I said rather than focus
on ancient personalities

00:05:46.146 --> 00:05:48.582 align:middle line:84%
of Hindu religion,
why not focus on modern

00:05:48.582 --> 00:05:51.151 align:middle line:84%
spiritual personalities
of the Hindu tradition, see

00:05:51.151 --> 00:05:54.321 align:middle line:84%
if they make sense to me.
And here I discovered if you

00:05:54.321 --> 00:05:59.093 align:middle line:84%
like real treasure because
I discovered certain modern

00:05:59.093 --> 00:06:03.397 align:middle line:84%
personalities who touched my
heart and captured my attention.

00:06:03.397 --> 00:06:04.832 align:middle line:90%
I'll give the names.

00:06:04.832 --> 00:06:07.701 align:middle line:84%
One was Ramana Maharshi
who lived in South India.

00:06:07.701 --> 00:06:11.739 align:middle line:84%
Here you see an individual lit
up, something has touched him,

00:06:11.739 --> 00:06:14.308 align:middle line:84%
something dramatic has happened
to him you can make out.

00:06:14.308 --> 00:06:17.678 align:middle line:84%
There's no artificiality,
he's not selling any gimmicks,

00:06:17.678 --> 00:06:20.948 align:middle line:84%
he's just, you know, established
in the real knowledge

00:06:20.948 --> 00:06:22.216 align:middle line:90%
of the spirits.

00:06:22.216 --> 00:06:24.284 align:middle line:84%
So you see this kind of
personality, but the personality

00:06:24.284 --> 00:06:27.521 align:middle line:84%
that stole my heart is a
personality called Ramakrishna

00:06:27.521 --> 00:06:33.427 align:middle line:84%
who lived in Bengal in the
1890s, 1880s I would say,

00:06:33.427 --> 00:06:36.497 align:middle line:84%
and his disciple Vivekananda,
really captured my attention

00:06:36.497 --> 00:06:38.732 align:middle line:84%
because here is a man who
had a similar journey.

00:06:38.732 --> 00:06:41.502 align:middle line:84%
He was an atheist in his
young days. He was in search

00:06:41.502 --> 00:06:44.438 align:middle line:84%
of spirituality, and he would
only accept spirituality

00:06:44.438 --> 00:06:48.308 align:middle line:84%
if he discovered some individual
who could claim the spirituality

00:06:48.308 --> 00:06:50.878 align:middle line:84%
as the matter of experience for
that person and wasn't a measure

00:06:50.878 --> 00:06:53.981 align:middle line:84%
of book learning or
intellectual acceptance.

00:06:53.981 --> 00:06:56.350 align:middle line:84%
So the journey that
Vivekananda took on of trying

00:06:56.350 --> 00:06:59.686 align:middle line:84%
to discover some individual
who is absolutely, you know,

00:06:59.686 --> 00:07:00.888 align:middle line:90%
embedded in the idea

00:07:00.888 --> 00:07:02.389 align:middle line:84%
of the spirit, not
just intellectually

00:07:02.389 --> 00:07:05.692 align:middle line:84%
but experientially is
what he was looking for,

00:07:05.692 --> 00:07:07.027 align:middle line:90%
that's what I was looking for.

00:07:07.027 --> 00:07:08.762 align:middle line:84%
So found my mentor
in Ramakrishna, Vivekananda.

00:07:08.762 --> 00:07:12.032 align:middle line:84%
So I was studying at
the Imperial College

00:07:12.032 --> 00:07:14.601 align:middle line:84%
in Kensington here
just around the corner

00:07:14.601 --> 00:07:17.471 align:middle line:84%
and while I was studying
physics I came across material,

00:07:17.471 --> 00:07:20.374 align:middle line:84%
the literature of
Ramakrishna, Vivekananda

00:07:20.374 --> 00:07:22.042 align:middle line:84%
that gave me the
thrill of my life.

00:07:22.042 --> 00:07:25.579 align:middle line:84%
It was the most life
transforming experience for me.

00:07:25.579 --> 00:07:27.314 align:middle line:84%
So studying the lectures,
et cetera,

00:07:27.314 --> 00:07:30.584 align:middle line:84%
of these two personalities were
not talking about spirituality

00:07:30.584 --> 00:07:32.286 align:middle line:84%
from some kind of, you
know, book learning

00:07:32.286 --> 00:07:36.690 align:middle line:84%
but actually first hand
encounter that image, you know,

00:07:36.690 --> 00:07:38.258 align:middle line:90%
that caught my attention.

00:07:38.258 --> 00:07:39.760 align:middle line:84%
So I was studying
their lifestyle.

00:07:39.760 --> 00:07:41.028 align:middle line:90%
While I was doing physics,

00:07:41.028 --> 00:07:43.730 align:middle line:84%
I was at the same time studying
spirituality represented

00:07:43.730 --> 00:07:47.234 align:middle line:84%
in this modern format, the
rational format, a format

00:07:47.234 --> 00:07:48.435 align:middle line:90%
that would appeal

00:07:48.435 --> 00:07:50.737 align:middle line:84%
to a commonsensical
person like me, a youngster.

00:07:50.737 --> 00:07:54.842 align:middle line:84%
>> Lilou: So never at any point
did it, was it counter,

00:07:54.842 --> 00:07:59.146 align:middle line:84%
not counterintuitive, but just
saying two separate things.

00:07:59.146 --> 00:08:00.514 align:middle line:90%
Science was saying one thing

00:08:00.514 --> 00:08:02.316 align:middle line:84%
and your studies
were saying another?

00:08:02.316 --> 00:08:03.884 align:middle line:84%
>> Lakhani: No, no, in
fact to the contrary.

00:08:03.884 --> 00:08:07.120 align:middle line:84%
I found that some of the issues
that science was struggling

00:08:07.120 --> 00:08:09.790 align:middle line:84%
with were better explored
by this deeper vision

00:08:09.790 --> 00:08:10.958 align:middle line:90%
of religion or spirituality.

00:08:10.958 --> 00:08:12.192 align:middle line:90%
I'll give you some examples.

00:08:12.192 --> 00:08:15.863 align:middle line:84%
For example, this particular
juncture we are talking

00:08:15.863 --> 00:08:19.066 align:middle line:84%
about quantum physics being
very exciting enterprise and

00:08:19.066 --> 00:08:22.402 align:middle line:84%
yet conceptually very
difficult to understand.

00:08:22.402 --> 00:08:26.540 align:middle line:84%
Suddenly I realized that what
spirituality is now telling us

00:08:26.540 --> 00:08:30.043 align:middle line:84%
is gives you a conceptual grasp
of what quantum physics is all

00:08:30.043 --> 00:08:32.211 align:middle line:84%
about, and this is the
heart of the matter.

00:08:32.211 --> 00:08:35.048 align:middle line:84%
It says that despite
appearances,

00:08:35.048 --> 00:08:37.951 align:middle line:84%
if you feel you can explain this
creation, this reality in terms

00:08:37.951 --> 00:08:41.889 align:middle line:84%
of matter and the epiphenomena
of matter means that attributes

00:08:41.889 --> 00:08:44.057 align:middle line:84%
of matter if you can
just link those things

00:08:44.057 --> 00:08:46.126 align:middle line:84%
up you can explain the
whole of this creation

00:08:46.126 --> 00:08:49.363 align:middle line:84%
then quantum physics
says, no, it's not true.

00:08:49.363 --> 00:08:51.698 align:middle line:84%
The underpinning to this
reality we guarantee

00:08:51.698 --> 00:08:57.137 align:middle line:84%
to be known material and
matter is an outer appearance.

00:08:57.137 --> 00:08:58.372 align:middle line:84%
This is, you know, Erwin
Schrodinger.

00:08:58.372 --> 00:09:01.575 align:middle line:84%
So this is dramatic material
to come out of physics

00:09:01.575 --> 00:09:03.577 align:middle line:84%
which is now telling
the physicality

00:09:03.577 --> 00:09:06.380 align:middle line:84%
of the physical world and
this fits extremely well

00:09:06.380 --> 00:09:09.716 align:middle line:84%
with a deeper vision of religion
that comes with Hinduism saying

00:09:09.716 --> 00:09:13.120 align:middle line:84%
that the underpinning to this
reality is not material, it is

00:09:13.120 --> 00:09:17.157 align:middle line:84%
essentially spirit
but when it manifests itself

00:09:17.157 --> 00:09:19.893 align:middle line:84%
